sequenceDiagram
    participant LI as libinput
    participant C as Compositor<br/>(event loop)
    participant EP as Event Pipe<br/>(pipe fd + JSON)
    participant E as Emacs<br/>(process filter)
    participant CQ as Command Queue<br/>(Vec + Mutex)
    participant IR as IM Relay<br/>(MPSC channel)
    participant App as Wayland Client

    Note over LI,App: Key ordering is preserved end-to-end via FIFO pipe and single-threaded consumers

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over LI,C: 1. Key Reception
        LI->>C: KeyboardEvent (keycode, state)
        C->>C: XKB lookup → keysym + UTF-8
        C->>C: text_input_intercept enabled?
        Note right of C: Intercept if: no Ctrl/Alt/Super,<br/>text input active, IM enabled,<br/>surface is not Emacs
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over C,E: 2. Compositor → Emacs (FIFO)
        C->>EP: serde_json → write JSON + newline
        EP-->>E: process filter triggered
        Note right of EP: Pipe fd delivers events<br/>directly to Emacs event loop

        loop for each JSON line in ewm--event-filter
            E->>E: json-parse-string → alist
            E->>E: Input method translation<br/>(per focused surface buffer)
            E->>CQ: ewm-im-commit-module(text)
        end
        Note right of E: Process filter processes<br/>all complete lines — each key<br/>fully handled before next
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over CQ,App: 3. Emacs → Client (FIFO)
        C->>CQ: drain_commands() pre-render + between outputs
        CQ-->>C: Vec<ImCommit> in push order
        loop for each ImCommit
            C->>IR: ImCommand::CommitString(text)
        end
        IR->>App: im.commit_string(text)
        IR->>App: im.commit(serial)
        IR->>IR: conn.flush()
        Note right of C: Focused output renders first.<br/>Commands arriving mid-render are<br/>processed between outputs, deferring<br/>remaining redraws to next VBlank.
    end

    Note over LI,App: Fast typing → keys buffer in pipe, process with latency but never reorder
